ut the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger Chetwode was born about 1388, in Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Chetwode, was 29 and his mother, Margery Dayvell, was 17. He married Margerey Crewe about 1414. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1388–Deceased":"umbes 1388–Surnud","1388–Male":"1388–Surnud","1392–Female":"1392–Surnud","1415–1485":"1415–1485","1361–1396":"1361–1396","1373–1399":"1373–1399","1415":"1415","Abt 1388":"umbes 1388","1399":"1399","1388":"1388","1485":"1485","1396":"1396","1373":"1373","about 1387":"umbes 1387","1361":"1361","1392":"1392","Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1388–Deceased":"noin 1388–Kuollut","1388–Male":"1388–Kuollut","1392–Female":"1392–Kuollut","1415–1485":"1415–1485","1361–1396":"1361–1396","1373–1399":"1373–1399","1415":"1415","Abt 1388":"noin 1388","1399":"1399","1388":"1388","1485":"1485","1396":"1396","1373":"1373","about 1387":"noin 1387","1361":"1361","1392":"1392","Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1388–Deceased":"environ 1388–Décédé","1388–Male":"1388–Décédé","1392–Female":"1392–Décédée","1415–1485":"1415–1485","1361–1396":"1361–1396","1373–1399":"1373–1399","1415":"1415","Abt 1388":"environ 1388","1399":"1399","1388":"1388","1485":"1485","1396":"1396","1373":"1373","about 1387":"envi